    "comment": "Rationale: Fig2F: Immunocytochemistry demonstrates that Snx14 colocalises with dendritic marker MAP2 in dissociated mouse cortical neurons.\nFig2E: Dissociated mouse cortical neurons were transfected with pZsGreen1-Snx14 plasmid and subsequently immunostained with mouse anti-SNX14 antibody and showed colocalisation with ZsGreen1. This indicates the specificity of the anti-SNX14 antibody.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The generic term \"synapse\" was used for this annotation as the paper only shows the presence of SNX14 puncta on dendrites.. Experimental description: C57BL/6 mouse (E15.5) cortices were dissected and used for immunocytochemistry.",
